. It feels like I’m zeroing in on the core issues.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring test coverage and macros**\\n\\nI’m considering whether including direct quasiquotes and removing the Toolbox could allow the test to pass, but I wonder about dynamic access. Perhaps a dynamic report could be generated by the agent during compileTestScala. I’m also thinking about the remaining call sites from ReificationMacros, since macros during test compilation might not be captured by the agent. It seems the TCK likely runs javaTest with the native-image agent, rather than during compilation. I need a test that invokes the macro at runtime, but that could be challenging with the Toolbox's speed limitations.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_rdkCbNgbN6R0BsqpGYYKSkDV|fc_04c3cf33d95e4f3d0169fc2860ce4c819ca316e81fa9e4db45", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.scalameta/parsers_2.13/4.9.3/src/test/scala/org_scalameta/parsers_2_13/ReificationMacrosTest.scala"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 6381, "output": 1260, "cacheRead": 26112, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33753, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778133068973, "responseId": "resp_04c3cf33d95e4f3d0169fc284e2bb4819cbb48af402e98d3f5"}}
